{% block ROLLBACK_PLAN %}
    h3. In case of release failure
    * Please ensure that the app (image-push) release execution was finished before infrastructure (mapping-update) release execution.
    * If shepherd release has failed, capture the shepherd error in CM ticket and contact the change reporter.
    * Proceed to rollback steps mentioned below.

    h3. Rollback CCM & CSI image mapping release - Cloning the precompiled releases

    Please use this table and the instructions as a reference to the precompiled rollback releases
    ||Step||Process||
    |1.|Please go to your devops portal, search for the "oke" project under shepherd and use the*oke-ccm-csi* flock|
    |2.|Click on "State History"
    <img src="state-history.png" alt="state history">|
    |3.|Select the appropriate execution target from the "Execution Targets" dropdown on the left. choose target as spectre.values.prd.<realm>.<region>
    Ex: spectre.values.prd.oc1.us-phoenix-1|
    |4.|From the list of states, select the state of Type: Apply (Final) from just before the latest roll-forward release. Note that if the roll-forward release for this CM was applied successfully, we want to select the second Apply (Final) type state from the list of states. The release ID should be different from the roll-forward release.
    <img src="rollback-state-history-1.png" alt="rollback state history">|
    |5.|Click on the Release ID link from the state info panel|
    |6.|Click on "Actions" -> "Clone release". Choose target as spectre.values.prd.<realm>.<region>. Ex: Ex: spectre.values.prd.oc1.us-phoenix-1
    Please wait for the release to finish planning|
    |7.|Wait for the release to succeed/fail
    * If release succeeds, continue post-release validation
    * If release fails, go to rollback step.|
    |8.|Click approve on the top right and enter this CM number and click Approve|

    h3. Mapping update rollback validation
    ||Step||Process||
    |1.|For each type of release for each of the flocks, the flock release must reach "Succeeded" phase|
    |2.|Open Limits Admin UI to check the property or limit you intended to change is done. Limits Admin UI is accessible from the devops portal[https://devops.oci.oraclecorp.com/limits-admin-ui/property-definitions]. Please realm specific endpoint for accessing the portal|
    |3.|Select the correct realm, group name is "{_}clusters{_}". Enter the individual property names|
    |4.|Choose the "group" as "Clusters" and choose the desired region and click on search|
    |5.|Please find the following properties and verify values with version {color:#00875a}{{ config2.k8s_versions }}{color} and mapping ccm-image-version-mapping, csi-image-version-mapping|
    |6.|Please validate that the mappings are matching to what was present in red in the rollforward infrastructure release (mapping-update) executed in the region.|
    |7.|Please repeat the Post-release validation for all the regions and realms|

    h3. Rollback CCM/CSI image push release
    * Since this flock pushes new images there is no need to do rollback, the use of the images which are already present is not affected.
    * If the images need to be absolutely deleted, login to OCIR in the Native Steward Tenancy by following this [Runbook|https://devops.oci.oraclecorp.com/runbooks/APS/artifact-push-service-aps/oke-native-steward-tenancies]
    * Search for the image which needs to be deleted and click delete

{%- endblock ROLLBACK_PLAN %}